label.value: Soluble Liver Antigen IgG Antibody Measurement

value.value: The determination of the amount of soluble liver antigen IgG antibody present in a sample.
The determination of the amount of smooth muscle IgG antibody present in a sample.
The determination of the amount of Streptococcus pneumoniae antigen present in a sample.
The determination of the amount of sulfate present in a sample.
The determination of the amount of taurine present in a sample.
The determination of the amount of total transforming growth factor beta in a biological specimen.
The determination of the amount of threonine present in a sample.
The determination of the amount of T-lymphocytes in a biological specimen.

label.value: Thyroid Stimulating Hormone Receptor Antibody Measurement

value.value: The determination of the amount of thyroid stimulating hormone receptor antibody present in a sample.
The determination of the amount of tyrosine present in a sample.
The determination of the amount of valine present in a sample.
A radiolucent and fracture-prone triangular zone in the proximal femur.
A method for measuring the molar concentration of a substance in solution by determining the freezing point of the solution.

A method for assessing bleeding time in which a controlled stab incision is made with a lancet on the earlobe or finger and blood is drawn off of the incision site with blotting paper every 30 seconds until bleeding stops.
An ultracentrifugation based method that uses enzymatic catalytic reaction to quantify a substance, which has been separated in solution by an ultracentrifugation process.
A non-invasive method to evaluate respiratory mechanical properties of the lung and airways using small-amplitude pressure oscillations superimposed on the normal, tidal breathing of a subject.

A non-invasive method to measure pulmonary resistance and reactance, and the impedance of the respiratory system, using small pressure oscillation of a regular square wave of pressure 5 times per second.

A method for assessing bleeding time in which the individual wears a blood pressure cuff inflated to 40mmHg, a controlled incision (10mm long x 1mm deep)is made on the volar surface of the arm, and blood is drawn off of the incision site with blotting paper every 30 seconds until bleeding stops.
An analytical technique wherein liquid chromatography is coupled to tandem mass spectrometry in order to separate, identify, and quantify substances in a sample.
An analytical technique where liquid chromatography with a fluorescence detector is used to separate, identify, and quantify substances in a sample.

A tablet formulation containing 5-ethynyluracil (GW776), an ethynyl derivative of uracil and the antineoplastic agent 5-Fluorouracil (5-FU) in a 10:1 ratio.  The GW776 portion of the tablet inhibits dihydropyrimidine dehydrogenase (DPD), the rate-limiting enzyme in 5-FU catabolism, thereby blocking degradation of 5-FU in the gastrointestinal tract and increasing the bioavailability of 5-FU. (NCI04)

A method for measuring the amount of ionizing radiation in a liquid substance. Samples are mixed with a mixture of solvent, surfactant and scintillators that can convert beta particles into light energy, which can be measured.
A method for measuring the flow of air through the bronchi upon expiration.
An electronic device used to measure the alkalinity or acidity of a liquid or semi-solid substance.
A method used to measure changes in volume, pressure and resistance within an organ or whole body by means of a plethysmograph.

A modification of the Ivy method for assessing bleeding time in which the individual wears a blood pressure cuff inflated to 40mmHg, a controlled incision is made using an automatic blade on the volar surface of the arm (thus standardizing the incision size), and blood is drawn off of the incision site with blotting paper every 30 seconds until bleeding stops.

A technique used to selectively replicate nucleic acid sequences from RNA templates using reverse transcriptase and RNA polymerase. Reverse transcriptase generates cDNA from the region of interest using primers and then RNA polymerase generates copies of the original RNA template.

label.value: Ultra High-performance Liquid Chromatography/Tandem Mass Spectrometry

value.value: An analytical technique wherein ultra-high performance liquid chromatography is coupled to tandem mass spectrometry in order to separate, identify, and quantify substances in a sample.
A genus of parasitic nematode in the family Ascarididae. A. lumbricoides is the largest intestinal roundworm infecting humans and is the causative agent of ascariasis.

A species of facultative anaerobic, Gram-positive, rod-shaped or elliptical coccobacillus in the family Coriobacteriaceae. It is commonly isolated from women with bacterial vaginosis and it is implicated in treatment failures.
A species of intraerythrocytic protozoan parasites in the family Babesiidae. B. divergens is transmitted by the tick Ixodes ricinus and it is the main causative agent of bovine babesiosis.
A species of intraerythrocytic protozoan parasites in the family Babesiidae. B. microti is transmitted by the tick Ixodes scapularis and is the primary causative agent of human babesiosis.

A species of a Gram-positive, aerobic, spore-forming bacillus in the family Bacillaceae. The species is positive for protease and lipase but negative for amylase, phosphatase, DNase, gelatinase and chitinase. B. pumilus is commonly found in soil and aquatic environments.
A species of anaerobic, Gram-negative, non-motile bacterium in the family Bacteroidaceae. B. salyersiae is a normal part of the gut flora and an opportunistic pathogen.

A species of a Gram-negative, anaerobic, rod-shaped bacterium in the family Bacteroidaceae. B. xylanisolvens is positive for degradation of xylan but negative for degradation of starch. It was isolated from human fecal samples.

A species of free-living amoeba in the family Balamuthiidae. B. mandrillaris is the causative agent of granulomatous amoebic encephalitis. It was isolated from the brain of a captive baboon and has not been definitively isolated in nature.
A calculated value based on all factors that influence the flow of gas from the airway opening to the alveoli, including airway resistance, and tissue resistance of the lung and chest wall.
A measurement of the airway conductance relative to lung volume.
Specifies whether any abnormality was present at birth or during the neonatal period.
An approximate calculation of the gestational age of the fetus.
A measurement of the total number of birth events at which the gestational age of the neonate is 37 weeks and 0 days through 38 weeks and 6 days.
A measurement of the total number of birth events at which the gestational age of the neonate is 39 weeks and 0 days through 40 weeks and 6 days.
Specifies whether any pregnancies resulted in miscarriages.
Specifies whether the subject's pregnancy has been confirmed.
A measurement of the total number of birth events at which the gestational age of the neonate is less than 37 weeks and 0 days.
Specifies whether any pregnancies resulted in stillbirths.
Specifies whether blistering occurred.
The longest diameter of an area of hardness in the skin.
